Knowledge within the graph is deeply recursive. We define the verification maturity of a compound or parent node $n_{\text{compound}}$ as strictly bounded by the minimum maturity of its downstream dependency cluster:

$$M(n_{\text{compound}}) \le \min_{n_i \in \text{deps}(n_{\text{compound}})} M(n_i)$$

An architectural assertion is only as mature as its least verified dependency. Because $G_t$ is strictly restricted to a DAG structure, this evaluation is guaranteed to terminate without encountering infinite recursion loops.

